\(\Rightarrow\,\,\,t\,=\,0\,\,\,\,\,\mbox{or}\,\,\,\,\,t\,=\dfrac{2u\,\sin\! \theta}{g}\,=\,T\)

#### Range, R

The maximum horizontal distance covered by the projectile is known as the horizontal range, \(R\).

\(R\,=\,\,v_{x}\,T\,=\,\left(u\,\cos\!\theta\right)\,\dfrac{2u\,\sin\!\theta}{g}\)

\(R\,=\,\dfrac{u^{\,2}\sin\!20}{g}\)

For a given speed of projection, \(u\), the horizontal range is maximum when

\(\sin\,20=1\,\,\Rightarrow\,\,\,\theta\,=\,45^{\circ}\)

thus maximum range, \(R_{\max}\,=\,\dfrac{u^{\,2}}{g}\)

